data.chText: 经济的；经济上的；经济学的
data.enText: connected with the trade, industry and development of wealth of a country, an area or a society

data.chText: 社会、经济和政治问题
经济增长 / 合作 / 发展 / 改革
政府的经济政策
经济史
目前的经济形势
有利可图的；可赚钱的；合算的

before.enText: of a process, a business or an activity

data.chText: 以上各词尤用于企业或国家的经济活动或状况。
data.enText: These words all describe activities or situations that are connected with the use of money, especially by a business or country.

data.chText: 指国家、地区或社会经济的、经济上的、经济学的：
data.enText: connected with the trade, industry and development of wealth of a country, an area or a society

data.chText: 这本书论及了那个时期的社会、经济和政治问题。
data.enText: This book deals with the social, economic and political issues of the period.

data.chText: 指财政的、财务的、金融的：
她陷入了财务困境。
data.enText: She had got into financial difficulties.

data.chText: 东京是主要的金融中心。
data.enText: Tokyo is a major financial centre.

data.chText: 指贸易的、商业的
data.enText: connected with the buying and selling of goods and services

data.chText: 指货币的、钱的，尤指一国的金融：
data.enText: ( formal or finance ) connected with money, especially all the money in a country

data.chText: 更为紧密的欧洲货币联盟
指财政预算的
data.enText: ( finance ) connected with a budget (= the money available or a plan of how it will be spent)

data.chText: 以上各词均指赚钱的、赢利的、有利可图的。
data.enText: These words all describe sb/sth that is making or is likely to make money.

data.chText: 指赚钱的、成功的：
data.enText: making a lot of money, especially by being popular

data.chText: 那出剧在百老汇大获成功。
data.enText: The play was very successful on Broadway.

data.chText: 公司又度过了一个兴旺发达之年。
data.enText: The company has had another successful year.

data.chText: 指有利润的、赢利的：
一家赢利很高的企业
指赢利的、以获利为目的的：
data.enText: [only before noun] making or intended to make a profit

data.chText: 这部电影票房收入不佳。
data.enText: The movie was not a commercial success (= made no profit) .

data.chText: 指生意或工作赚大钱的、获利多的：
data.enText: (of business or work) producing or paying a large amount of money; making a large profit

data.chText: 他们在利润丰厚的海外市场上生意很多。
data.enText: They do a lot of business in lucrative overseas markets.

data.chText: （常用于否定句中）指（工序、业务或活动）有利可图、可赚钱、合算：
data.enText: (often used in negative sentences) (of a process, business or activity) producing enough profit to continue

data.chText: 附近的一家超市开业后，当地的小商店就没有利润可赚了。
data.enText: Small local shops stop being economic when a supermarket opens up nearby.

data.chText: economic意为与国家、地区、社会或个人经济有关的：
data.enText: Economic means ‘connected with the economy of a country or an area, or with the money that a society or an individual has’.

data.chText: 政府的经济政策
生育孩子在经济方面的问题
data.enText: the economic aspects of having children

data.chText: economical意为经济的、节俭的、节约的：
data.enText: Economical means ‘spending money or using something in a careful way that avoids waste’.

data.chText: 大量购买洗衣粉通常要省钱些。
data.enText: It is usually economical to buy washing powder in large quantities.

simple_means.memory_skill: eco 生态；经济 + nom …学 + ic …的 → 经济（学）的

tr: using the minimum of time or resources necessary for effectiveness
example: an economic use of home heating oil
an economical use of her time
it was no longer economic to keep the factory open
have to keep prices high enough to make it economic to continue the service

tr: concerned with worldly necessities of life (especially money)
example: he wrote the book primarily for economic reasons
gave up the large house for economic reasons
in economic terms they are very privileged

tr: of or relating to the science of economics
of or relating to an economy, the system of production and management of material wealth
example: aspects of social, political, and economical life

value.def: Economic means concerned with the organization of the money, industry, and trade of a country, region, or society.

example.ex: The pace of economic growth is picking up.
example.tran: 经济增长的步伐正在加快。

example.ex: Small English orchards can hardly compete economically with larger French ones...
example.tran: 英国的小型果园很难在经济上和法国的大型果园竞争。

example.ex: Economically and politically, this affair couldn't come at a worse time.
example.tran: 无论从经济上还是政治上来看，这件事来得都太不是时候了。

value.def: If something is economic, it produces a profit.

example.ex: The new system may be more economic but will lead to a decline in programme quality.
example.tran: 新系统可能更合算，但是会降低程序质量。

value.boxu_tran: 注意不要混淆 economic, economical, economics 和 economy。
value.boxu_usage: Take care not to confuse economic, economical, economics, and economy.

trans: 经济移民(以找工作或寻求更高生活水平为目的)
